  "title": "A Lord's Charge Before the Caspian Blockade",
  "summary": "On the observation deck of the V2SD Nemesis, the Sith lord Aldus Thel summons stormtrooper Lieutenant Loreck Hawkins to assign him a mission ahead of the coming Caspian blockade. Thel reflects on the failures of the earlier Caspian Annexation Campaign under Rellik, explaining that he intends to break the Caspian people's will rather than merely defeat their army, exposing the Democratic Union's treaty violations and arms shipments to the Rebel Alliance to turn the populace against its own leaders. He charges Hawkins to select eight men and lead them in covert support of Agent Cooper to obtain physical proof of the illicit shipments, likely by infiltrating a starport warehouse or freighter, while remaining undetected. Thel grants Hawkins tactical command and promises both personal accountability and commensurate reward. The lieutenant accepts eagerly and departs to prepare his men.",
